<methods>
<methodStep>
<description>
<section>
<title>Experimental Design</title>
<para>Three replicates of each soil were sampled in each site.</para>
</section>
<section>
<title>Methods</title>
<para>FIELD:  We sampled three cores of organic and mineral soil horizons from four high northern latitude ecosystems located in arctic tundra and boreal forests within Alaska, USA. Sites included recently burned and unburned black spruce forests near Delta Junction in interior Alaska, moist acidic tussock tundra and non-acidic tundra near Toolik Lake. Soil sampling was conducted on 24 July 2001 for the tundra and 5-13 July 2006 for the black spruce forests.   LAB:  We measured CO2 production of seven soils during a 924-day laboratory incubation.  Soil samples were subjected to two treatments, nitrogen addition (with and without) and soil warming (5 degC and 15 degC).</para>
</section>
